ids_alerts.rule_category: Malware Command and Control Activity Detected
ids_alerts.rule_raw: alert http $HOME_NET any -> $EXTERNAL_NET any (msg:"ET MALWARE StealC_V2 CnC Activity (POST)"; flow:established,to_server; urilen:<24; http.method; content:"POST"; http.uri; pcre:"/^\x2f(?:[a-z0-9]{14,19})\x2ephp$/"; http.header_names; bsize:67; content:"|0d 0a|content-type|0d 0a|host|0d 0a|content-length|0d 0a|connection|0d 0a|cache-control|0d 0a 0d 0a|"; nocase; fast_pattern; http.content_type; content:"application/json"; http.content_len; bsize:3; pcre:"/^\d{3}$/"; http.connection; content:"Keep-Alive"; http.header; content:"Cache|2d|Control|3a20|no|2d|cache"; http.request_body; pcre:"/^(?:[a-zA-Z0-9\x2b\x2f\x3d]){100}/"; classtype:command-and-control; sid:2066280; rev:1; metadata:affected_product Windows_XP_Vista_7_8_10_Server_32_64_Bit, attack_target Client_Endpoint, tls_state plaintext, created_at 2025_12_11, deployment Perimeter, deployment SSLDecrypt, malware_family Stealc, performance_impact Moderate, confidence High, signature_severity Major, tag c2, updated_at 2025_12_11, mitre_tactic_id TA0011, mitre_tactic_name Command_And_Control, mitre_technique_id T1071, mitre_technique_name Application_Layer_Protocol; target:src_ip;)

ids_alerts.rule_msg: POLICY-OTHER HTTP request by IPv4 address attempt
ids_alerts.rule_raw: alert tcp any any -> any $HTTP_PORTS ( msg:"POLICY-OTHER HTTP request by IPv4 address attempt"; flow:to_server,established; http_header; content:"Host:",fast_pattern,nocase; pcre:"/^Host\x3a\s*(?:(?:25[0-5]|2[0-4][0-9]|[01]?[0-9]?[0-9])\.){3}(?:25[0-5]|2[0-4][0-9]|[01]?[0-9]?[0-9])\s*:?\s*\d*\s*$/ims"; service:http; reference:url,www.w3.org/Protocols/rfc2616/rfc2616-sec15.html; classtype:policy-violation; sid:50447; rev:1; )

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Load Of RstrtMgr.DLL By An Uncommon Process
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Detects the load of RstrtMgr DLL (Restart Manager) by an uncommon process.
This library has been used during ransomware campaigns to kill processes that would prevent file encryption by locking them (e.g. Conti ransomware, Cactus ransomware). It has also recently been seen used by the BiBi wiper for Windows.
It could also be used for anti-analysis purposes by shut downing specific processes.

signature_matches.name: packed with generic packer
signature_matches.description: anti-analysis/packer/generic
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: packed with generic packer
    namespace: anti-analysis/packer/generic
    authors:
      - william.ballenthin@mandiant.com
    scopes:
      static: function
      dynamic: unsupported
    att&ck:
      - Defense Evasion::Obfuscated Files or Information::Software Packing [T1027.002]
    mbc:
      - Anti-Static Analysis::Software Packing::Standard Compression [F0001.002]
    examples:
      - Practical Malware Analysis Lab 18-01.exe_:0x409dc0
  features:
    - and:
      - or:
        - mnemonic: pusha
        - mnemonic: pushad  # vivisect
      - or:
        - mnemonic: popa
        - mnemonic: popad  # vivisect
      - characteristic: cross section flow
      - not:
        - match: contain pusha popa sequence

signature_matches.name: packed with UPX
signature_matches.description: anti-analysis/packer/upx
signature_matches.rule_src:
rule:
  meta:
    name: packed with UPX
    namespace: anti-analysis/packer/upx
    authors:
      - william.ballenthin@mandiant.com
    scopes:
      static: file
      dynamic: file
    att&ck:
      - Defense Evasion::Obfuscated Files or Information::Software Packing [T1027.002]
    mbc:
      - Anti-Static Analysis::Software Packing::UPX [F0001.008]
    examples:
      - CD2CBA9E6313E8DF2C1273593E649682
      - Practical Malware Analysis Lab 01-02.exe_:0x0401000
  features:
    - or:
      - and:
        - format: pe
        - or:
          - section: UPX0
          - section: UPX1
      - and:
        - format: elf
        - or:
          - string: "UPX!"
